title: Bug 10593: Jar export should add ".jar" suffix if not specified
OB: When selecting some files in Build 20020228 and exporting them using the jar export feature, if the user enters "test" as the jar name, it currently creates a jar file called "test" instead of "test.jar".
EB: The jar export feature should add the ".jar" suffix if it is not specified by the user.
SR: Add a check in the jar export feature to append the ".jar" suffix to the filename if it is not already present.
